[14] I. Lesanovsky, M. van Horssen, M. Guta, J, P. Garrahan, Phys. Rev. Lett. 110, 150401 (2013)</gtr:description><gtr:exploitationPathways>The results of my research are mainly theoretical, and contribute to the mathematical foundation of Quantum Statistics. The development of such a theory is highly relevant for the successful implementation of Quantum Technologies, which is a field of high interest with potentially revolutionary applications. 

My group is currently working with the experimental group of R. Blatt in Innsbruck to use the statistical methodology in analysing experimental data. Additionally, our results on Quantum Metrology are directly relevant for the design of quantum sensing devices operating close to the quantum limit.</gtr:exploitationPathways><gtr:id>FCA2E469-BF1F-46C6-8F88-5DB92E81B01F</gtr:id><gtr:outcomeId>5464a2277a54d2.47633965</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:sectors><gtr:sector>Aerospace, Defence and Marine,Digital/Communication/Information Technologies (including Software)</gtr:sector></gtr:sectors></gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication><gtr:id>5F4D295A-4C78-4A51-B189-3F850FD1E0E0</gtr:id><gtr:title>Characterization of dynamical phase transitions in quantum jump trajectories beyond the properties of the stationary state.</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Physical review letters</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/4bf3d91b851cc36c8e394cb00c517068"><gtr:id>4bf3d91b851cc36c8e394cb00c517068</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Lesanovsky I</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2013-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:issn>0031-9007</gtr:issn><gtr:outcomeId>56deb9e9cf6921.37762254</gtr:outcomeId></gtr:publication><gtr:publication><gtr:id>25982417-8C1A-40FF-B636-D444C482C2F0</gtr:id><gtr:title>Maximum likelihood versus likelihood-free quantum system identification in the atom maser</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Journal of Physics A: Mathematical and Theoretical</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/9b17492a9621469a320cbbea0b227fc6"><gtr:id>9b17492a9621469a320cbbea0b227fc6</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Catana C</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>201